items.content:
@lulumeservey I was a public face of Microsoft for a while and wrote its first social media policy and helped with the media training of various people. 

For myself, the best media training I got was going on TV. Because if you are getting on TV, like the BBC, ABC News, Fox, or whatever, you probably are only going to get one to three minutes of airtime. You have to make sure that you say something interesting in those few minutes. It is a skill that is gained over time.

This conversation reminds me of going on a panel discussion with Mike Arrington, who started TechCrunch. As we were going on stage, he turned to me and said, "Hey, now it is our job to entertain people. So what are we going to fight about?"

@yeswola @elonmusk One of these costs a few dollars an hour to operate. You add a human, and the cost goes up to more than $20.

And that's wholesale, which you triple the price for retail. That is why an Uber for an hour drive is usually $60-$100, somewhere around there.

The Cybercab will eventually be a lot less.

@JackEllis @hustlin_heev Yes agreed that too, we might be reaching the limits of a solo indie founder without a team and without funding

